where

formula_140

The coefficients formula_141 are complex variables. We can treat them as coordinates which specify the state of the system, like the position and momentum coordinates which specify a classical system. Like classical coordinates, they are generally not constant in time, and their time dependence gives rise to the time dependence of the system as a whole.

The expectation value of the Hamiltonian of this state, which is also the mean energy, is

formula_142

where the last step was obtained by expanding formula_138 in terms of the basis states.

Each formula_141 actually corresponds to &quot;two&quot; independent degrees of freedom, since the variable has a real part and an imaginary part. We now perform the following trick: instead of using the real and imaginary parts as the independent variables, we use formula_141 and its complex conjugate formula_146. With this choice of independent variables, we can calculate the partial derivative

